Combine sugar, cocoa, Karo and sour cream in pan and add to melted oleo.
Cook 3 or 4 minutes (soft ball in cold water).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Place pan in cold water for 2 minutes.
Add chopped nuts.
Beat until it looks thick. Use an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.

title: summer squash and zucchini casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl; mix well. Pour into greased 9-inch square baking dish. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Press firmly into ungreased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake about 1 hour; let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
(Can microwave for 18 to 20 minutes.)

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except ground beef; mix well.
Add ground beef; mix lightly but thoroughly. Press into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan; bake 1 hour.
Drain; let stand 5 minutes.

title: afternoon delight(broiled crabmeat sandwiches)
directions: Combine crabmeat, green pepper, onion, olives and salt.
Mix together, mayonnaise, lemon juice and horseradish until well blended; add to crabmeat mixture.
Place on toast slices.
Top with cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: stuffed tomato salad
directions: Scald tomatoes and remove the skins. Cut a slice from the top of each and with a small spoon, remove the seeds. Peel the cucumbers and cut them into dice. Season highly and mix with at least half the dressing. Fill the tomato cups with this and put a spoonful of the dressing on top. Sprinkle a very little finely chopped parsley over and serve on a bed of lettuce leaves.

title: strawberry chiffon pie
directions: Mix together the strawberries, Jell-O, sugar and eggs.
Boil over hot heat for 5 minutes.
Chill.
Pour evaporated milk into a large bowl.
Place in freezer until crystals form around the bowl. Beat with mixer until stiff.
Fold in cold mixture.
Mix well. Place in graham cracker crusts and chill.

title: barbecued roast
directions: Place roast in Dutch oven.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over roast.
Cover and bake at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: blueberry lemon bread
directions: Cream butter, gradually add 1 cup sugar, beat at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with milk.
Begin and end with flour mixture.
Stir in lemon rind, then fold in blueberries.
Pour batter in 8 x 4 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until pick comes out clean.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and lemon juice in small saucepan.
Heat until dissolves. Puncture top of bread with toothpick.
Pour lemon juice over warm bread, allowing to soak in.
Cool for at least 30 minutes.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Blend lemon juice and condensed milk together. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling salted water until tender; drain. Arrange stalks in a greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayo, lemon juice and curry. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs and butter; sprinkle over all.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Trim with pimento strips.
To make in microwave oven, cook on High for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: grandma fends' date cookies
directions: Combine dates, 1/2 cup sugar and water.
Bring to boil; add nuts and cool.
Cream butter; add brown and white sugars.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to butter.
Chill. Roll out dough.
Spread with date mixture.
Roll back up.
Let chill.
Cut and bake at 350° about 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: chicken oriental
directions: Mix soup, milk, chicken, onion, celery and water chestnuts in 3-quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; keep warm.
Mix Bisquick, water and soy sauce until soft dough forms.
Gently smooth dough into ball on well floured board. Knead 5 times; roll out.
Cut into 1 to 1 1/2-inch squares.
Pour chicken mix into a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Melt margarine and brush on top of dough squares.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°.

title: blender impossible pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and blend on high while counting to 10 slowly.
Pour into a well-greased 10-inch pie pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: apple drop cookies
directions: Sift flour with baking soda, salt and spices into large bowl. Stir in walnuts, apple and raisins.
Set aside.
Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and cider; beat until combined.
Stir in flour mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven about 8 minutes until golden brown.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: buttermilk yeast rolls
directions: Crumble yeast into warm water in large mixing bowl.
Stir to dissolve.
Add buttermilk and sugar; let mixture stand 15 minutes. Add warm butter and eggs; mix.
Sift soda and salt with 4 cups of flour; add to liquid mixture.
Beat until smooth and batter forms. Add remaining sifted flour, stirring with spoon until dough is no longer sticky.
Knead on floured board.
Place in large greased mixing bowl.
Cover; let rise until double, about 1 hour.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done, then drain.
Cut boiled eggs up in small pieces.
Crumble bacon up.
Chop onion.
Cut tomatoes up in small pieces.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Add salad dressing, then refrigerate.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Sprinkle sugar over top of cranberries and let stand over night.
Mix grapes, pineapple, nuts and marshmallows with cranberries.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Sift flour along with dry ingredients.
Add shortening and cut in with a knife or pastry cutter.
Add yeast to buttermilk and mix thoroughly.
Roll dough as for biscuits.
Cut to desired size.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 450° for 10 minutes.
Unused dough may be kept in refrigerator.

title: pea picking cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° in 3 or 4 layers.
Let cool.

title: barbecue rice
directions: Melt butter.
Add celery and onions.
Cook slowly until tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add the soup, broth, mushrooms and liquid smoke.
Add the cooked rice.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: eggnog bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with eggnog.
Fold in pecans, raisins and chopped cherries.
Bake in a loaf pan, approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Combine and blend with mixer (low to medium speed) the sugar, oil, vanilla and pumpkin. Add eggs, one at a time, and blend.
Add baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add flour and nuts. Blend on medium to high speed until batter is smooth.
Pour batter into ungreased 11 x 16-inch (or similar size) jelly roll pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: salmon stew
directions: Slice potatoes, onions and carrots; place them in a large pot and cover with water.
Add butter, salt and pepper; then cook vegetables until almost done.
Stir in salmon and soup.
Turn off heat.
Stir in milk and serve.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix potatoes, eggs, flour, onion, salt, pepper, and garlic. In a skillet heat the oil and butter together until hot. Shape the mixture into patties and fry in hot oil until golden brown. Serves about 6.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together; cover and refrigerate overnight. Serve with fresh crisp vegetables.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Spray cookie sheet with vegetable pan spray. Layer out potato slices. Lightly brush potato slices with oil. Sprinkle garlic powder and paprika over potato slices. Bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: holiday crescent braid
directions: Roll each part of dough into rectangle, 15 x 6-inches, on a lightly floured board.
Spread each with half the butter.
Place on greased baking sheets.
At 1-inch intervals on long sides of rectangles, make 2-inch cuts with scissors.

title: eggplant and tomatoes
directions: Peel and slice eggplant.
Alternate layers of eggplant and tomatoes in 2-quart baking dish until full.
Cover with wax paper. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Drain.
Mix sauces together and pour over eggplant mixture.
Put under broiler and brown (you can cook eggplant and tomatoes in microwave also).

title: lemon bar
directions: Mix like cookie dough.
Press in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: chinese cabbage salad
directions: Salad:
Slice green onions.
Mix cole slaw, onions, sunflower seeds, almonds and noodles.

title: potato latkes *
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add matzo meal, salt and pepper. Grate onions and potatoes (after peeling) and place in colander. Run boiling water through to help retard color change.
Mix onions and potatoes in bowl with egg mixture.
Fry in oil until brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes about 14 medium size latkes.

title: tender beef tips
directions: Trim fat off stew beef.
Place meat in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine remaining ingredients; pour over stew beef.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 250° for 6 hours.
(I often cook this in a crock-pot.
It is just as good done that way.)
This dish can be served with rice or noodles.

title: hamwiches
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Press 1 package rolls in bottom of pan.
Mix cheese, milk, eggs, mustard and pepper together.
Divide mixture in half.
Add diced ham to 1/2 cheese mixture.
Spread ham mixture on top of crescent layer.
Spread second package of crescents on top of ham mixture.
Spread remaining cheese mixture over crescents.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown.
Cut in squares.

title: baked cod
directions: Cut cod into serving pieces.
Place fish in lightly greased baking dish.
Pour melted margarine over fish.
Top with Parmesan cheese, pepper and paprika.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: sesame carrot sauce
directions: Push garlic through press.
Combine with ginger, stock, soy sauce, honey and seed in a small dish.
Microwave, uncovered, on High until bubbly, about 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Toss with cooked broccoli or other vegetables; sprinkle on carrot.
Serve warm as a side dish or slightly chilled on lettuce as a salad.
Serves 4.

title: fried tomatoes
directions: Dress up veggies by adding simple ingredients to canned or frozen English peas:
pearl onions, sliced mushrooms, sliced almonds or lemon pepper, singly or in combination.

title: hot turkey salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise and soup.
Mix the rest of the ingredients and spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mayonnaise and soup mixture evenly over the top.
Bake 15 minutes in 450° oven.

title: rocky road candy squares
directions: Melt chocolate chips, Eagle Brand and butter over low heat in medium saucepan.
Stir together.
Pour over the following ingredients which you have measured into a large bowl: peanuts and marshmallows.
Mix and fold until all covered.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish which is buttered and lined generously with wax paper.
Chill until firm.
Lift out, peel back the paper and slice uniformly into squares.
To serve, bring to room temperature.
Stores well, covered, in refrigerator.
This is the easiest, best candy to make and eat.
Great for Christmas treats.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Let strawberries, sugar and eggs boil for 2 minutes (stirring the 2 minutes).
Remove and add Jell-O.
Set aside and let cool. Beat the Carnation milk until it stands in peaks (may add a little lemon juice until stands in peaks).
Fold into Jell-O mixture. Pour into 2 graham cracker crust pie shells.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix thoroughly sugar, shortening and eggs.
Sift together and stir in flour, cream of tartar and baking soda.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon.
Place 2-inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: blueberry or cherry dessert
directions: Mix and bake Jiffy cake according to instructions on box.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese, vanilla pudding and milk. Beat this well, until smooth.
Pour this over the cooled cake. Now, put pie filling on top of this.
Now spread Cool Whip on top. Sprinkle top with finely chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: turkey divine
directions: Cook turkey legs until tender.
Remove meat from bones.
Cook broccoli 9 minutes on High in microwave, stirring halfway through. Mix rest of ingredients together.
Arrange broccoli in sprayed casserole dish.
Top with meat.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: molded chicken salad
directions: Prepare the Jell-O with water, including the vinegar and onion salt.
Cool.
Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice and sour cream.
Pour Jell-O mixture slowly into mayonnaise mix.
Chill until it begins to set, then add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate in 7 3/4 x 12-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serves 12.

title: good bye chicken(my mother's recipe, adapted for microwave)
directions: Pour milk into 6 to 8-cup glass measure.
Heat at 70% power for 3 1/2 minutes.
Remove from oven; set aside.
Place butter and half of the salt and onion salt in 2 cup glass measure; place in oven. Heat on High for 45 seconds.
At pause, stir flour into butter until smooth.
Return to oven and cook on High for 45 seconds. Remove from oven, briskly stir in warm milk and pepper.
Cook on High 3 to 5 minutes until of consistency of cream soup, stirring every 2 minutes.
Pour Minute rice into buttered 2-quart microwave dish.
Combine chicken broth and remaining salt; pour over rice. Sprinkle half of the cheese over rice.
Top with asparagus, then chicken.
Pour on sauce.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cook on 70% power, uncovered, for 10 to 12 minutes, until cheese is melted and sauce bubbling.
Top with slivered almonds and serve.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Cook peas 10 minutes and set aside.
Dilute soup with chicken broth.
Cover bottom of casserole dish with peas.
Sprinkle eggs over peas.
Crumble 4 or 5 crackers over this.
Repeat layers. Pour chicken soup over top and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake in 300° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: corn and cheese bake
directions: Combine eggs and sour cream in a large bowl; stir in corn and next 5 ingredients.
Pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and bake until cheese melts.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: overnight salad
directions: Spread mayonnaise over peas.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bacon bits.
Cover with foil and leave in refrigerator overnight.
Do not mix any of this until the next day, then mix and eat.

title: extra creamy fudge
directions: Stir together margarine, sugar and milk in a heavy saucepan. Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly. Boil 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in chocolate until melted. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch or 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool to room temperature
and cut into squares.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a 5-quart freezer.
Fill to line on freezer with milk.

title: cajun creole
directions: Place chicken breasts in a Dutch oven.
Cover with 3 quarts of water.
Salt and pepper, bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer about 3 hours.
Shell, devein and wash shrimp.
Place in a pot of boiling water.
Cook 6 minutes (until shrimp turns pink).
Remove from water and drain.
Place in bowl in refrigerator.
Remove chicken from broth and cool.
Add shrimp, rice, sausage (cut into bite-size pieces), chicken bouillon and chopped onion.
Pour liquid from stewed tomatoes into chicken broth.
Slice tomatoes and add to Creole.
When chicken has cooled, remove skin and debone; tear chicken into small pieces and add to mixture.
Add okra, cut into one-inch pieces, crushed red pepper and gumbo file.
Cover and cook until rice is tender.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: date nut pudding
directions: Put dates and butter in mixing bowl.
Pour boiling water over and soda and allow to cool a bit.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour into a greased or wax paper lined 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake in slow oven for 1 hour at 325°.
Garnish with warm lemon sauce or whipped cream (Cool Whip).

title: heavenly hash
directions: Combine pineapple, strawberries, milk and Cool Whip together until all ingredients are blended together.
Add marshmallows and nuts; chill for 1 hour.

title: homemade ranch style dressing
directions: Stir all of the dry ingredients listed; store in an airtight container.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix together all ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Put in casserole.
Top with cheese and chips. Bake, uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes or until bubbly.

title: mint-wine lamb chops
directions: Set oven on broil; trim fat from chops.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Brush chops with wine mixture.
Place lamb on rack in broiler pan.
Broil 3 to 4 inches from heat about 4 minutes or until brown.
Brush again with wine mixture.
Turn chops and brush the other side.
Broil 5 to 7 minutes longer for medium doneness (160°).
Makes 8 servings.

title: buttermilk pie 1
directions: Beat eggs. Combine buttermilk, flour, sugar, oleo and vanilla. Blend well. Bake 10 minutes at 275°; increase to 300° for 50 minutes. Use unbaked pie shell.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together sour cream and baking soda and set aside.

title: family favorite casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions in skillet; add tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Combine next 5 ingredients.

title: strawberry brownie torte
directions: Grease two 9-inch round layer cake pans.
Line with wax paper, extending up sides of pans.
Grease wax paper.
Prepare brownie mix as package directs for cake-like brownies.
Put into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until top springs back when touched.
Cool, then put this together just like a strawberry shortcake:
one layer of brownie, next half of strawberries, then half of the whipped topping, then another layer of brownie, then rest of whipped topping, then rest of strawberries.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: carrot-broccoli medley
directions: Place
margarine, salt, nutmeg, carrots and broccoli in 1-quart casserole.	Cover tightly and microwave on High (100%) for 4	minutes;
stir.
Cover	and microwave until vegetables are crisp-tender, 2 to 4 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: jack's favorite salsa dip
directions: Put all the ingredients into a large saucepan.
Dice the onion or chop it in a blender.
Sugar the mix to suit your taste.
Bring to a boil, then let it simmer for 18 to 20 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: broiled or grilled turkey steak
directions: Blanch turkey in boiling water for 2 minutes.
Remove from water; pat dry.
Rub the steaks on all sides with mustard. Sprinkle on the tarragon and pepper.
Grill or broil 5 to 6 inches from the heat source, in middle of grill (high heat) until cooked through, about 5 to 10 minutes on each side.
Serve warm or slightly chilled.

title: cake in a cone
directions: Follow directions on the box to prepare the cake batter. Place cones in ungreased muffin pans.
Fill cones about 1/2 full (1/4 cup) - do NOT overfill the cone or batter will overflow and bake on the sides of the cones.

title: chicken cordon blue
directions: Flatten each breast to 1/4-inch thickness.
Place one slice ham and cheese on top of chicken.
(Do it in that order). Sprinkle with parsley and pepper.
Roll and fasten with toothpick. Dip in egg and roll in crumbs.
Brown in oleo.
Place in casserole.
Combine soup, sour cream and mushrooms and pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: tommie's pie crust
directions: Mix the flour, sugar and salt.
Sift together.
Add the Crisco. Mix with electric mixer until it resembles corn meal, then add the cold water.
Shape into 2 balls and roll out thin with a rolling pin.
Simple enough for anyone to make!
To cut down on fat, use 3/4 cup Crisco.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread sour cream on bottom of a 10-inch quiche or pie plate. Can also use a large platter.
Layer taco sauce on top of sour cream.
Sprinkle with lettuce.
Add tomatoes, olives, and onion. Top with cheese.
Scoop up with Tostitos.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on the package.
Drain.
Melt 1/2 to 3/4 stick butter and cheese.
Stir butter and cheese until creamy smooth.
Mix with broccoli and pour into buttered casserole.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers which have been added to melted stick of butter.
Warm in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, egg yolks and small amount of milk until mixed well. Then add remaining milk with vanilla, margarine and coconut. Cook on medium heat until thickened. Pour into baked pie shell.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Mix and bake in greased pan 1 hour at 350°.
Add 2 cans cherries after 1 hour and bake again for 15 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix everything together and pour into 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with buttered corn flake crumbs the last 15 minutes of baking time.
This can be mixed a day ahead and refrigerated until ready to bake.

title: wedding soup
directions: Make ground meat and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese into small meat balls.
Drop meat balls into boiling chicken broth.
Add spinach and noodles.
Cook to boiling for 5 minutes.

title: six layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add ingredients by layer. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan before serving.

title: "solo" poppy cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add Solo poppy filling. Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Blend in vanilla and sour cream. Sift together flour, soda and salt. Add gradually to Solo poppy mixture, beating well after each addition. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into greased 9 x 10-inch tube pan which has the bottom lined with wax paper. Bake in moderate oven at 350° about 1 hour and 15 to 20 minutes. Remove from pan and peel off paper. Decorate by sifting confectioners sugar through a paper doily.

title: fillets in red sauce
directions: Heat oil in pan; add next 5 ingredients and saute until beginning to soften.
Add next 4 ingredients and simmer until soft.
Remove from pan and puree.
Return half of sauce to pan; add fish in single layer if possible and top with remaining sauce and olives.
Simmer until fish is cooked.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in refrigerator for a few hours.
Actually is better prepared day before serving and keeps well in refrigerator.

title: pizza pecan pie
directions: Roll crust on pastry cloth or lightly floured bread wrapper. Spread crust on pizza pan; make sure that there are no holes in crust.
Mix ingredients except for Karo syrup and pour into unbaked crust.
Dribble syrup over top of mixture.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until top is crusty.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Press with fork to make crisscross pattern.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour into uncooked 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: aunt ella's cookies
directions: Mix soda and warm coffee in molasses.
Mix eggs and spices. Beat sugar and butter.
Add molasses mixture last.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place beef in bottom of baking pan.
Place chicken on top of beef.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Mix sour cream and mushroom soup together and pour over meat.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes longer.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Pour in deep dish pie shell. Bake 15 minutes at 425°, then 35 minutes at 350°.

title: lila smith's slaw
directions: Grate
cabbage, a little onion and celery.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Add celery seed.

title: old fashioned chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in frozen pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
First, mix together 2 sticks of butter and the sugar.
Add the eggs, then slowly add the plain flour, whipping cream and vanilla flavoring.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a greased tube pan; put into a cold oven.
Bake at 300° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Check with toothpick for doneness.

title: icebox banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to recipe on box.
Add the softened cream cheese to pudding.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer mix with bananas and vanilla wafers in large bowl.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours before serving.
This makes a lot.
Recipe can be cut in half.

title: italian soup
directions: Cut sausage in chunks and brown.
Pour off fat; saute onions and green pepper to soft.
Add garlic, parsley, oregano, basil, tomatoes and pepper.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Before serving turn up heat and add bow tie macaroni.
Cook until tender.

title: gerald warmouth's easy whole wheat bread
directions: In blender, blend 2 cups water and 2 packages yeast.
Let stand for about 4 to 5 minutes to dissolve.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder and cook. Pull chicken apart and layer bite size chicken with broccoli. Pour the cooked mixture over layers as you build.
(can be frozen).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Put into 2-quart greased casserole. Melt 1/2 cup butter.
Blend in flour and gradually add milk and bouillon cubes.
Pour over broccoli.
Heat water and butter until melted.
Pour over stuffing and toss with walnuts.
Place on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake salmon and beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and place in a greased loaf pan.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Lightly grease a 9x13 inch casserole; pour in pineapple and juice. Add flour and sugar. Blend 1/2 cup cheese, crackers, and melted margarine. Mix
together. Add remaining cheese on top. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: quick hollandaise sauce *
directions: In small saucepan with wire whisk, stir together all ingredients until smooth.
Stir over medium-low heat until thick. Do not boil.
Serve over vegetables, seafood or poached eggs. Sprinkle with paprika.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: tater-dipped veggies
directions: In a small bowl, combine potato flakes, Parmesan cheese, celery salt, garlic powder and butter.
In another bowl, beat eggs.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend shortening, sugar and egg.
Add all other ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chile con queso
directions: Cook onions and garlic in oil until softened.
Drain oil.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until cheese melts on low heat. Cut cheese in chunks for easier melting.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: savory harvest cabbage
directions: Melt shortening in Dutch oven or frying pan.
Add cabbage and stir over medium heat until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Serves six to eight.

title: shrimp rice
directions: Make a white sauce with first 7 ingredients; add shrimp and sherry.
Serve over rice.

title: velvet salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill in mold (about 1 hour) before serving.

title: cedric's casserole
directions: Fry onion in margarine.
Add hamburg, salt and pepper.
Heat through but do not brown.
Spread 3 cups of cabbage in a greased casserole.
Cover with meat mixture and place the remaining cabbage on top.
Pour can of tomato soup over all.
Bake covered in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: potato puffs
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine potatoes and eggs and add to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop from tablespoon into 1/2 cup shortening and fry until brown on both sides.
Can be served with syrup.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix Cool Whip, Fluff and cream cheese with mixer.
Dip strawberries in brown sugar.
Place strawberries in serving plate and serve with mixed Fluff, Cool Whip and cream cheese as a dip.

title: bowknot hot rolls
directions: Mix yeast in warm water.
Set aside.
Combine milk, sugar, shortening and salt; mix well.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour.
Beat well. Add yeast and egg.
Gradually add remaining flour, forming soft dough.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until double (about 1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Knead and pinch off a small amount of dough.
Roll a strip about 6-inches long.
Tie in bowknot.
Bake in preheated oven at 450°.

title: breakfast cranberry-apple crumble
directions: In a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish, combine apples and cranberries.
Mix sugar and 2 tablespoons flour; toss with fruit. In a bowl, combine oatmeal, pecans, 1/2 cup flour and sugar.
Stir in margarine.
Spoon over fruit.
Bake at 350° in oven for 45 minutes.
Garnish with cranberries and pecans.
Serve at breakfast topped with cream or over vanilla ice cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: zucchini-chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream together sugar, brown sugar and margarine.
Beat in egg, vanilla, flour and baking soda.
Blend together zucchini, nuts and chocolate morsels and stir into mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie pan about 2 inches apart.
Bake about 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown in 350° oven.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Combine ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and cook for 6 to 8 minutes.
Stir well and allow to stand a few minutes.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes; cut into quarters.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a bag.
Moisten potatoes with water and shake a few at a time in bag, coating pieces well.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Place potatoes in a layer in pan.
Bake at 375° for about an hour, turning once during baking.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: stuffed shells - florentine
directions: Heat marinara sauce. Spoon 1 cup of sauce into bottom of a large pan or maybe 2 pans.
Reserve remaining sauce.
Cook spinach as directed on pkg. Drain well and mix with ricotta cheese, egg, oregano, nutmeg and parmesan cheese in a large bowl.

title: fresh green beans with lime and ginger vinaigrette
directions: Steam fresh green beans until firm and crunchy.
Add sliced almonds and cherry tomatoes.
Pour dressing over beans and toss gently.
Serve at room temperature.

title: shrimp and crab salad
directions: Place cream cheese and tomato soup in double boiler.
Melt, stirring, until smooth.
Soften gelatine in cold water.
Dissolve in hot water, then stir into soup mixture.
Add seasonings and let partially set.
Add 1 can white crabmeat and 1/2 cup fresh, cooked shrimp, cut in small pieces.
Let partially set, then add mayonnaise, onions, celery and olives.
Stir until well blended and place in salad mold.

title: poor man cake
directions: Beat together sugar, oil and vanilla.
Sift together flour, cocoa and salt and add to previous ingredients.
Add cold water. Mix well.
Add vinegar.
Bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza
directions: Simmer tomato juice and seasonings until almost thick.
Add rest of ingredients, except for the bread and cheese.
Simmer until thick.
Toast pita bread under the broiler on both sides so it is a little crisp.
Put on pizza mixture.
Add cheese; put under broiler to melt cheese.

title: grandma faraudo's creamed tuna on toast
directions: Melt margarine in 2-quart saucepan. Add flour and mix quickly into a paste (remove from heat to avoid scorching).
Slowly add milk and continue to mix to blend. Return to moderate heat, stirring slowly.
When it starts to thicken, remove from heat and add tuna and pepper.
Heat through.
Spoon over slices of toast, biscuits or English muffins.

title: pearl's strawberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello with boiling water.
Then add strawberries and juice, pineapple with juice and nuts.
Mix.
Pour half into 13 x 9-inch pan or mold.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour to firm.
Leave remaining jello mixture out on counter.
Spread sour cream over chilled jello.
Pour remaining mixture on top of sour cream. Chill.
Makes 8 cups.

title: diabetic - yogurt fruit dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and yogurt.
Blend until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Carve balls from your favorite melon and serve with toothpicks to accompany this tasty dip.
Dip makes 2 cups or 8 servings (4 tablespoons per serving).

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
Melt morsels and butter; stir in crumbs and nuts.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch.
Press firmly to line bottom of pan.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mash butter with hot potatoes. Beat in sugar, eggs, vanilla and milk. Add salt to taste; add nutmeg. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until it won't shake when moved. Do not overcook; it will firm as it cools.

title: meringue
directions: Combine 1/4 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt in a saucepan; stirring constantly.
Add water and cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Cool completely. Beat egg whites at high speed of an electric mixer until foamy. Gradually add remaining 1/4 cup of sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until soft peaks form.
Add vanilla and cornstarch mixture. Beat until stiff peaks form, enough for one 9-inch pie.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Soften 1 stick oleo, crumble 1/4 pound crackers into butter and mix.
Pour over vegetables.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients except rolls.
Place 1 tablespoon of the mixture on the middle of a crescent roll.
Bring edges of the crescent roll ove top of mixture and pinch together.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with chicken gravy.

title: coffee nip
directions: In a 2-quart bowl, sprinkle gelatine over Amaretto or almond extract and water.
Let stand 1 minute to soften; stir to dissolve. Add coffee and sugar.
Stir until mixture is clear.
Pour into 8 sherbet glasses.
Cover and chill until firm.
Garnish with Cool Whip and almonds.

title: pie crust
directions: Use enough
water to make a soft dough.
The softer you can handle
the dough the better the crust.
This makes enough dough for 5 or 6 pies.
If the scraps get too dry and stiff to roll, just
work a little water into them.
They will still be flaky if rolled thin.

title: egg noodles with madcap sauce
directions: Heat oil over medium heat; add onion, garlic and beef and cook until beef is browned. Drain excess fat. Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, salt, pepper and oregano. Cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cook noodles as directed on package. Drain. Serve sauce over noodles.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place layer of whole graham crackers in bottom of pan.
Beat pudding and milk. Add the container of Cool Whip and mix well.
Pour half the pudding mixture over the layer of crackers.
Top with another layer of crackers.
Pour remaining half of pudding over the crackers and top with another layer of crackers.

title: milk punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve chilled.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix crackers, sugar, oleo and peanut butter; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread evenly over mixture. Let cool.
Cut as desired.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix dry onion soup, mushroom soup, dry red wine and whole mushrooms together.
Pour over raw stew meat.
Mix well.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Cover tightly.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: broiled french fries
directions: Preheat broiler.
Line broiler pan with aluminum foil.
Drop potatoes into a large pot of boiling water.
Partially cover. Return to boiling and cook 4 minutes.
Drain. Toss in a large bowl with butter.
Arrange potato wedges in single layer on prepared pan.
Sprinkle with half the cheese. Broil 5 to 10 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Turn potatoes.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan.
Broil 5 to 8 minutes longer or until golden brown. Season with salt and pepper.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: orange cheese salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill until firm.
Stir once while chilling.

title: memama's glazed fruit
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: cinnamon pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers, water and lime for 24 hours, then drain and soak in ice cold water for 3 hours.
Drain again.
Add cucumbers and add water to cover top.
Heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Soak for 2 hours.
Drain.
Throw away mixture.

title: hurry up english trifle
directions: Make gelatin according to package directions plus rum flavoring.
Cut cake into 1-inch cubes and place them in the bottom of your serving bowl.
Pour the slightly cooled gelatin mixture over the cake and refrigerate until set firm.
Whip cream and 2 tablespoons of sugar until stiff and spoon over the top; swirl with a spatula.
Sprinkle with grated chocolate.
Delicious, light and easy.

title: curry spiced rice
directions: In 3-quart casserole dish, combine onion and butter.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap; microwave on High for 3 minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients; cover and microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Stir well.
Cover and microwave for another 20 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed.
Let stand 4 to 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: microwave bread pudding
directions: Microwave milk and butter on High for 3 minutes in a 9-inch round microwave dish. Stir in eggs, sugar, cinnamon, vanilla and raisins.
Stir to blend.
Add bread pieces and let soak for a minute or two.
Microwave on High for 7 minutes.
Let set 5 minutes before serving.

title: marshmallow pineapple icebox dessert
directions: Dissolve marshmallows in warmed, but not boiled milk.
Cool slightly.
Add whipped cream, pineapple and nuts.
Mix wafers and butter; pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save a few crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Put pineapple mixture in pan.
Let stand in refrigerator 12 hours.

title: irish coffee cake
directions: Beat butter and 4 ounces sugar until white and creamy.
Add beaten eggs and mix together.
Mix in flour.
Pour into oblong baking pan and bake at 325° for about 50 minutes.
Turn onto wire rack and cool.
Make coffee.
Add gelatin, brown sugar and whiskey and pour evenly over cake.
Chill about 1 hour.
Spread the whipped cream over cake.
Decorate with grated walnuts.

title: steak casserole
directions: Salt steak; pound in flour.
Cut steak in 1-inch cubes.
Brown in skillet.
Put in casserole dish and add potatoes, carrots and onion soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: double chocolate bundt cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour 12-cup Bundt cake pan.
Blend cake mix, sour cream, water and eggs on low speed until moistened.
Beat for 4 minutes on medium speed.
Fold in chocolate pieces; pour into pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until cake springs back when touched lightly in center.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Spread cake with Caramel Glaze allowing some to drizzle down sides.

title: grilled fin grouper with butter pecan sauce
directions: Combine chopped shallots, white wine, heavy cream, salt and pepper in medium saucepan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium.
Simmer and stir until mixture is reduced to about one-third.
Whisk in butter a tablespoon at a time until all is melted; strain, then add salt and pepper to taste.
Add roasted pecans.

title: barbecued baby beef ribs
directions: Tips:
This basting sauce is good also for chicken, turkey legs or ground meat patties.

title: escalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Cut ham into 1/2-inch cubes.
Pare and slice potatoes.
Heat milk to boiling; add ham and potatoes, and again heat to boiling. Add salt if tenderized ham is used.
Turn into a greased 6 or 8-cup baking dish; dot with the butter cubes.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Ham cubes are more flavorful if pan fried before adding to the potatoes.

title: dessert delight
directions: Beat milk and Cool Whip together.
Drain pineapple and put in whip mixture.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Refrigerate for about an hour.

title: one-step pound cake
directions: Grease and flour fluted or tube pan.
Combine the ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into pan. Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.
Cool upright in pan 15 minutes.
Remove and eat!
May glaze with lemon icing.
Delicious served with fruit flavored sherbet.

title: asparagus with lime hollandaise
directions: Trim woody stems from asparagus.
Bring 2 quarts of water to a boil.
Add salt.
Add asparagus and boil 6 to 8 minutes until firm-tender.
Arrange ham on 4 plates.
Drain and divide asparagus on plates.
Put yolks in top of double boiler and beat with juice from lime and cook over medium heat until double in volume. Drizzle in butter.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour in "strips" over asparagus.
Garnish with grated egg.

title: deluxe apple pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie pan with pastry.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and cinnamon.
Add to apples and mix thoroughly.
Set aside.
Crush pears and spread in bottom of pastry lined pan.
Sprinkle with rum. Heap apple mixture over pears.
Dot with butter.
Put on top crust and seal.
Crimp edges.
Cut slits for steam to escape.
Bake in 400° oven for 45 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: grits casserole(8 to 10 servings)
directions: Cook grits according to directions on package.
Cut up butter and cheese roll and add to grits while hot; mix well.
Beat eggs and add enough milk to make 1 cup.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour into buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Add Cheddar cheese last few minutes (optional).

title: hot cranberry casserole
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and put into a greased casserole dish.
Mix together the margarine (melted), 1/2 cup nuts, the brown sugar and the oats.
Place on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken with onion until tender; remove to cool.
Add to chicken broth the soup and butter.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a rolling boil and add dumpling squares one at a time.

title: hungarian potato soup
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Add potatoes, salt and 1 cup water.
Cover and cook 15 minutes or until tender.
Blend flour, paprika and sour cream until smooth.
Stir into potato mixture.
Add milk and heat until boiling, stirring.
Cook 1 minute and season to taste.

title: brown sugar casserole pudding
directions: Sprinkle sugar over bottom of deep 1 1/2-quart casserole. Spread both sides of bread with margarine; cut in 1/2-inch cubes and arrange over sugar.
Sprinkle with raisins.
In a medium size bowl, beat eggs slightly with wooden spoon or whisk.
Beat in cinnamon, milk, rum or bourbon, vanilla and salt.
Pour over raisins.
Place in shallow pan; add hot water to pan to come 1-inch up sides of casserole.
Bake in 350° oven 60 to 70 minutes until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Remove
from water; let stand 10 minutes.
Loosen pudding at edges with thin knife.
Spoon into bowls.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked sea bass in filo with julienne vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt 1/2 oz. butter in a frying pan and gently fry the mushrooms for 2-3 minutes until just softened. Remove from the heat and season.
Set aside to cool.
Melt half the remaining butter in a small saucepan.
Lay the filo sheets out on the work surface and brush with melted butter.
Fold each sheet over and brush again.
Lay a fish fillet in the centre of each, season and top each with some of the mushrooms and chopped parsley.
Fold over two opposite corners of pastry and then bring up the other two to form a parcel scrunching and twisting them together as they meet in the middle.
Press gently to seal and then transfer to a baking sheet.
Brush with butter and bake for 20-25 minutes until crisp, golden and cooked through.

Meanwhile, peel the carrot and cut into very thin sticks, or coarsely grate. Trim the courgette (zucchini) and cut or grate in the same way. Trim the leek, slice in half lengthwise, and run under water to flush out any trapped earth.
Shake well to remove excess water and then shred finely.
Set aside.
Five minutes before the sea bass is cooked, melt the remaining butter and stir-fry the prepared vegetables for 2-3 minutes until just tender.
To serve, divide the shredded vegetables between two warmed serving plates and season.
Top each pile of vegetables with a parcel of fish and serve with wedges of lemon to squeeze over.

title: peanut butter breakfast bar(weight watchers)
directions: Mix thoroughly; form into bar on foil and freeze.
Eat frozen (if you can wait!)
Equals 1 bread, 1 milk, 1 fruit, 1 fat and 1 protein.

title: puffy shrimp tempura
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Dip shrimp or vegetables in batter and deep fry.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup cheese for top. Mix all ingredients together. Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes or so.

title: seven-layer mexican dip
directions: Mash avocados in a bowl with lemon juice, salt and pepper. In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning.
On a large flat plate, spread bean dip in a large circle.
Top with avocado mixture, then sour cream mixture. Follow this with onions, then tomatoes, followed by olives.
Cover all with grated cheese.
Chill until ready to serve with corn chips.

title: quick and chewy crescent bars
directions: Unmold can
of	rolls and place rectangles in ungreased 15 x 10-inch
jelly
roll pan.
Press dough to cover bottom of pan and seal
perforations.
Pour
milk over dough.
Sprinkle with frosting
mix.
Drizzle
with the melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Cool.
Cut into squares. Makes 3 to 4 dozen bars.

title: cool cream of corn soup
directions: Place all ingredients in medium-sized saucepan.
Bring to boil, cover and simmer on low for 20 minutes.
Puree in blender or food processor until smooth.
Stir and taste.
If too thick, add a dash of water to thin slightly.
Ladle 8 ounces of soup into each bowl.

title: cheesy spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender.
In saucepan, warm soup and cheese until cheese melts.
Add drained spaghetti noodles.
Serve as side dish.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Drain well.
Saute onion and celery until tender, but not brown.
Mix all ingredients.
Reserve 1 cup cheese.
Sprinkle with Accent, celery salt and pepper, then mix.
Place in buttered pans.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: j. r.'s meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into jelly roll on aluminum foil.
Wrap roll in foil and bake for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for 30 more minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before slicing.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Blend yeast and water together well.
Then add beaten egg, milk, sugar, oil, salt and flour.
Mix well and refrigerate.
Use when needed.
Let rise 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until brown.

title: cheezy hot dog
directions: Make a split in the hot dog and fill it with cheese.
Place hot dog in bun.
Wrap hot dog loosely in a paper towel.
Microwave for 35 seconds on High.

title: kurt's peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix butter, milk and sugar in pan; bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes or to 234° on thermometer.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter chips, Fluff and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: In
large
bowl
mix
half and half, sugar and vanilla. Stir in
whipping cream.
Freeze in 4 quart ice cream freezer as directed.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: ham and potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve cold.

title: asparagus party "pin-wheels"
directions: With rolling pin, roll out bread slices until they are flat. Mix together cream cheese, Cheddar cheese and egg until smooth and creamy.
Spread this mixture on bread slices.
Place one asparagus spear on each bread slice.
Roll up.
Melt butter in pan and dip each pin-wheel lightly in the butter.
Place rolls in pan until they are almost frozen.
Slice with very sharp knife into bite size pieces.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.
(May be frozen and baked at a later date at same temperature but for approximately twice the time.)

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter, sugar and egg.
Blend all dry ingredients.
Stir into shortening.
Chill dough.
Roll dough in balls (1 1/4-inch).
Place 3 inches apart on greased pan.
Flatten with a fork dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.

title: clam stuffed mushrooms(makes 20 appetizers)
directions: Remove and finely chop mushroom stems.
Brush caps with melted margarine; place in shallow pan.
In skillet, cook celery, pepper, onion, mushroom stems, pimiento and bouillon in margarine 5 minutes; add remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture into caps; bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until hot.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Put the sugar, vinegar, salt, turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed in a large pot.
Boil for 5 minutes. Add the alum. Add the zucchini, peppers and onions. Bring to rolling boil.
Set off stove.
Place in hot jars and seal.

title: fruit cooler
directions: Add raspberry flavored drink mix and sugar to pineapple juice. Stir to dissolve.
Add remaining fruit juices.
Chill and serve over ice.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage and pour off fat.
Layer a greased casserole with bread, sausage and cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over mixture in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
This may be assembled and refrigerated to be baked the next day.

title: portuguese soup
directions: Brown stew meat; add water with onions, carrots, stewed tomatoes, potatoes, beans, string beans and corn.
Add salt and pepper to taste; boil over medium flame for 1 hour, then add rice, cabbage and tomato sauce.
Simmer on low flame about 20 minutes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all together.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in hot water and cool.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients and pour into mold. Refrigerate until set.
Serve with crackers.

title: english cherubs
directions: Combine 1/2 cup brown sugar, butter, flour and dash of salt in a medium mixing bowl.
Mix until well combined (mixture will look dry).
Press in bottom of a greased 9-inch square pan.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add remaining brown sugar, 1/2 cup sugar, vanilla and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Mix well.
Stir in coconut and pecans. Spread over layer in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is set and lightly browned.
Cool; cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: vanilla fudge
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until soft ball forms in cold water (at least 20 minutes after it starts to boil).
Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Mix well together and pour into buttered dish.
Place in fridge to cool, then cut into squares.
Keep in fridge or a cool place.

title: hot beef sandwiches(makes 100 sandwiches)
directions: Place roasts in roaster (may be left whole or cut up as stew meat).
Add spaghetti sauce, dill pickles and juice.
Add enough water to cover the meat. Cover and cook until meat is able to break apart easily, at 350° for approximately 6 hours.
May be done in slow oven overnight.

title: rotini
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger, then combine all ingredients except cheese and noodles.
Prepare rotini noodles in pot of boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Mix sauce with cooked noodles.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into a casserole dish.
Layer with 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese, then mixture and top with remaining cheese.
Bake for 40 minutes or until cheese is melted and golden brown.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix slightly beaten eggs, corn, cooking oil and buttermilk. Sift together corn meal, salt and baking powder.
Add to egg mixture.
Pour half the batter into greased baking dish.
Put layer of cut up hot chilies, then layer of cheese over batter.
Add remaining batter.
Cheese may be sprinkled over top.
Bake 25 minutes in 450° oven.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Slice okra and salt to taste. Combine flour and meal; stir together. Coat okra with meal mixture and fry in vegetable oil until almost done. Chop tomatoes and stir remaining meal and flour on tomatoes. Add to okra and fry until brown. (Do not stir often.)

title: buckeye candy
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Add eggs, singly, beating well after each addition.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until tender and drain.
Add next four ingredients.
Pour in greased casserole dish.
Mix margarine and corn flakes together.
Put on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry upside-down pudding
directions: Pour washed blueberries into buttered casserole (1 1/2-quart size) and sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar. Cream shortening, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 egg together.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Add this to creamed mixture alternately with 1/2 cup milk. Pour batter over blueberries. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Spoon out while hot and serve with cream, whipped cream, ice cream or milk.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: miss elsie's jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: applesauce fruit cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar together.
Add applesauce and eggs.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Add last 4 ingredients.
Mix all together.
Bake in a tube pan with wax paper in it for 4 hours in a 200° to 250° oven.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Drain oysters, reserving liquid.
Crumble crackers.
Mix oyster liquid with about equal amounts of milk and the mushroom soup and heat on slow burner.
Add drained oysters to the crackers, cubed cheese, and chopped broccoli.
Lightly stir in the liquid mixture.
Turn into sprayed ovenproof dish and bake uncovered in 400° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Season chicken with garlic and onion season.
Melt stick of butter in large skillet; add onion and bell pepper.
Saute.
Add green chillies and evaporated milk.
Stir. Add both soups.
Blend well in skillet.
Place a layer of Doritos in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add 1/2 of cooked chicken to pan.
Pour 1/2 of soup over chicken and top with grated cheese.
Repeat procedure. Cover with foil and place in oven for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: sealeg soup
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Thinly slice celery.
Melt butter in heavy pan.
Add potatoes and celery.
Barely cover with water. Cook until tender.
Add milk.
When scalded add sealegs and heat until scalding.

title: easy method lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
In a large bowl, mix together tomato juice, sauce, paste, onion, oregano, basil, salt, pepper, garlic, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in meat.
Spread 1/3 cup meat sauce over bottom of dish.
Place 1/2 the uncooked noodles over the sauce and top with 1/2 cottage cheese and then half of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers and cover with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Microwave at Medium for 35 minutes, uncovered.
Place remaining Mozzarella cheese on top and continue microwaving at Medium for 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix jello and hot water until dissolved.
Add cold water and frozen strawberries and refrigerate until lightly thickened.
Mix crushed pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°, then cool.
Beat together 1 cup sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled pretzel layer.
(This layer can be doubled.)
Then put strawberries on top.
Set in fridge for at least 12 hours.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix together. Store in refrigerator.

title: poppy seed cake(bundt)
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, oil, water and eggs together until smooth, then add poppy seed (stir in).
Put cinnamon-sugar at bottom of greased (shortening)
Bundt pan, then put mix in.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars. Add eggs and vanilla, and beat well.

title: chocolate cake icing
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa thoroughly. Add milk and oleo. Place over heat and boil until it spins a thick thread. Remove from heat. Add vanilla. Beat for about 2 minutes with mixer. Spread between layers, on top and sides of cake.

title: cheesy beef cornbread
directions: Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of cornmeal in bottom of well-greased 10-inch skillet (iron skillet works best).
Cook beef first in another pan and drain.
Combine Jiffy mix with milk, corn and eggs and mix well.
Pour 1/2 batter into skillet.
Sprinkle other ingredients on batter.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: easy mexican casserole
directions: Remove paper from tamales and cut in 1-inch pieces.
Drain corn and combine all ingredients, except cheese.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole and top with grated cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: anchovy and artichoke pasta
directions: Saute garlic and anchovies in oil.
Quarter artichoke hearts and add to pan.
Add clam juice, wine and basil.
Bring to boil; simmer 3 to 4 minutes, then toss with cooked pasta.

title: pull taffy
directions: Cook in a pan over medium heat until the hard crack stage (a string will harden and crack when dropped into cold water).
Pour into a buttered pan or use several dinner plates.
Cool candy until you can handle it.
Take a handful of the taffy from the pans (it will be honey colored).
Keeping your hands well buttered, start pulling taffy out into a string and roping it back together.
Taffy will turn whiter as it is pulled and get stiffer and harder to pull.
Once it is white enough and seems to be stiff enough to hold its shape, pull out into a long rope and lay on waxed paper.
Cut the ropes into bite-sized pieces and wrap in the paper.
Twist the ends and store.

title: hot spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach. Drain well.
In a baking dish, add cream cheese, mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese and spinach.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 1/2 hour.
Serve with Pepperidge Farm sesame sticks or any other cracker.

title: broccoli surprise salad
directions: Combine the broccoli flowerets and rings of sliced onion. Just before serving, add a dressing made of:
mayonnaise, sugar and wine vinegar.
Pour dressing over salad only when ready to serve.
Toss and add peanuts and raisins.
Toss again.
Serve right away.

title: carrot salad
directions: Scrub carrots well but leave skin on.
Grate into a big bowl; add raisins.
Sprinkle a little lemon juice over the mixture. Pour honey or corn syrup over salad until it tastes right.

title: southwest appetizer
directions: Soften cream
cheese and spread out evenly in glass pie plate. Add can
of chili on top.	Distribute green chilies on top of chili.
Sprinkle
cheese
over all.
Warm in microwave until cheese melts
or
put
in
oven
until warm.
Serve with tortilla chips, potato chips or crackers.
"MMM" good!

title: carol's mud bugs
directions: Pour Chex cereal into large bowl; set aside.
In a 1-quart microwave-safe bowl, combine next 3 ingredients.
Microwave High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth, stirring after 1 minute.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereal.
Stir until all pieces are evenly coated.
Pour cereal into large Ziploc bag with powdered sugar. Seal and shake until all pieces are evenly coated.
Spread on wax paper to cool.

title: forgotten roast
directions: Place roast on a large piece of aluminum foil and arrange vegetables around roast.
Sprinkle meat and vegetables with dry onion soup mix.
Spoon undiluted mushroom soup on top.
Wrap loosely with foil, making sure it is sealed at top and sides. Place
in a roaster pan and bake at 275° for 4 hours or 325° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: gram's cheese pie
directions: Beat all ingredients on high until well mixed.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Bake fast for 15 minutes at 425°, then slow for 45 minutes at 350° until crust is brown and custard is set.

title: caesar salad
directions: Put oil in pan; heat.
Take pieces of bread, put in pan and sprinkle parsley and garlic salt.
Cook until brown.
Remove from oil.
Put in paper towels.
Remove grease.
Place in brown bag to drain rest of grease off.
Mix lettuce and dressing, then croutons.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Shred cheese and mix all ingredients. Form into 1-inch balls.
Bake 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet until golden brown.
For a firmer texture, add an extra 3 c. of biscuit mix and an extra 2 c. of cheese to above listed ingredients.
Makes about 6 doz. and can be frozen if uncooked.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together; chill and roll into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts. Serve with crackers.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion. Drain.
Mix other ingredients together and add the hamburger meat and onion.
Simmer for at least 1 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake 60 minutes in a 350 degree oven.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute onions, peppers and mushrooms in melted oleo.
Then, add other ingredients.
Put in greased baking dish and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the crab, and simmer over low heat until thoroughly heated.
Stir in the crabmeat and serve. Yields 2 cups.

title: yum-yum salad
directions: Boil sugar in water. Add Jell-O and pineapple. Let stand to cool. Fold in cheese, Cool Whip, nuts and marshmallows. Let set to congeal. Stir occasionally as it begins to set. May be served as a salad on top of lettuce or as a dessert.

title: ham and corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan,
over medium-high heat, saute bacon until nearly crisp.
Remove and drain on paper towels; set aside. Remove all but 1/4 cup drippings from saucepan.
Add celery, onion, green pepper and garlic.
Saute over medium-high heat for 5 minutes. Add potatoes and broth.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Place 2 cups of the corn and 1/2 cup of the milk in a blender.
Cover and blend until pureed.
Add pureed corn, remaining corn, ham and potatoes. Simmer for 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

Stir in remaining 3 1/2 cups milk, 1 tablespoon of the parsley, salt, pepper and hot pepper sauce. Bring to just under boiling. Serve and garnish with reserved bacon pieces and remaining 2 tablespoons parsley.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, potato water, egg, milk and yeast, then add potato and stir together.
Add flour.
Knead and put in refrigerator and cover.
Make off and let rise in warm room.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and water and bring to a boil.
Add the lemon juice.
Fill 7 quarts with apples, sliced, and pour syrup over apples.
Seal.
Cool pack for 20 minutes.

title: lelia's gingerbread
directions: Pour water over shortening.
Add sugar, molasses and egg; beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Spray 8-inch pan with Pam.
Place in 350° oven 35 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: chicken breasts with wine and mustard
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Saute the breasts in 4 tablespoons butter 3 to 5 minutes, on each side until browned. Remove from pan.
Saute the shallots briefly.
Add wine, cream and stock; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook until sauce is thickened.
Whisk in mustard.
Whisk in remaining 2 tablespoons butter.
Return chicken to the sauce and heat through.
Place chicken on platter and spoon sauce over it and top with a twist of pepper from the mill.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt margarine in 2-quart casserole. Mix flour and sugar well, then add milk and mix well.
Pour into casserole.
Pour peaches on top.
Bake for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: salmon pate
directions: Drain, debone and flake the salmon. Mix together with all other ingredients except garnishes.
On a pretty platter, mold mixture into a fish shape.
Arrange almonds to resemble scales. Use slice of olive for eye and thin strips of celery for the tail. Garnish with parsley. Chill until serving time.
Serve with buttery crackers.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Yields 16 servings. Low in salt, sugar and fat.
Very good for diabetics.

title: cheeseburger-vegetable casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add all other ingredients, but hold back 1/2 cup cheese for topping.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: instant mince pie
directions: Mix all in bowl and fill crust.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: scallop and vegetable cheese casserole
directions: In a large skillet heat 2 teaspoons oil.
Add onions and garlic; saute for 2 minutes.
Add bread crumbs and cook until lightly browned.
Remove from heat; add 3 tablespoons Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Spread evenly over bottom of ovenproof baking dish.
Layer half of Mozzarella cheese on top.
Then add layer each of zucchini, carrots, spinach and scallops.
Sprinkle with basil, salt and pepper.
Layer remaining Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Brush remaining oil over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and continue to bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cottage cheese and pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jellos in boiling water.
Add cold water and pineapple.
Stir Miracle Whip into cottage cheese and add to jello-pineapple mixture.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: summer sauce
directions: Clean and boil until thickens.
Use on chicken or spaghetti.

title: easy klobasniky (sausage rolls)
directions: Thaw bread dough completely, but don't let rise.
Cook sausage in boiling water for 15 minutes.
Cut sausage into 8 pieces, then slice each piece in half lengthwise.
Drain out grease on paper towels.
Cut bread dough into 16 pieces.
Wrap sausage slices into bread pieces, pinching together.
Use flour on hands.
Place rolls, seam side down, in 9 x 13-inch pan which has been sprayed with Pam. Let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Makes 16.

title: roquefort or blue cheese salad dressing
directions: Makes 1 quart.	Beat
all
ingredients,
except cheese, with mixer.
Crumble cheese into dressing.
Store in refrigerator, covered, until ready to use.
Shake well before serving.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix all except cheese and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Put cheese and liquid in blender for 1 to 2 minutes. Dip can be served hot or cold.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Melt almond bark and add chocolate chips.
Add peanuts.
Drop with teaspoon on wax paper.

title: orange stir-fry chicken
directions: Trim fat from chicken breast halves. Cut into 1/4-inch strips. Mix soy sauce, 1 teaspoon cornstarch, the ginger root and garlic in medium glass or plastic bowl. Stir in chicken. Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: beef tips and gravy
directions: Take 2 pounds of beef tips, cut into small cubes.
In a frying pan, put 2 tablespoons butter or oil and beef tips.
Brown tips with salt and pepper to taste.
After tips are brown, add 1 1/2 cups water; lower temperature and put lid on pan.
Cook meat until tender.
When meat is tender, remove from pan and leave liquid. Add 1 1/2 cups water and 4 to 5 tablespoons of Bisquick and mix, making a gravy, then add meat back in and cook 15 to 20 minutes.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix flour, oats, baking powder and salt.
Beat egg with honey and milk.
Pour egg into oats.
Stir until just mixed.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour, 15 minutes.

title: holiday lizzies
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and eggs.
Sift flour and soda together and add to egg mixture.
Stir in milk.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 80 or 90 cookies.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a bowl. Cut in peanut butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add oats, egg and milk, stirring only until blended.
Pour batter into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Cool.
Cut and serve with jelly.

title: best ever lasagna
directions: Brown beef and add next six ingredients.
Cook, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Meanwhile, mix remaining ingredients and cook noodles. Slice Mozzarella.

title: pasta con broccoli
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water for about 4 minutes. Drain and return to pan.
Add cream, butter, garlic, tomato sauce, and broccoli.
Bring to a boil for about 4 to 5 minutes.
When noodles are done, stir in mushrooms to heat.
Remove from heat and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Toss and serve immediately.
Makes 2 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a large saucepan, add the celery soup, chicken soup and milk.
Heat at medium heat, while stirring.
In a large casserole dish, add the chicken breasts.
Spread the butter over the top and then sprinkle on the garlic powder.
Preheat the oven to 375°.

title: southern style mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes and boil until tender.

Drain well. Put in a bowl and add butter, mayonnaise, salt and pepper to taste. Mash with electric mixer for just about a minute and then add about a 1/4 cup milk. Continue to mash until desired smoothness.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In a small bowl beat eggs and sugar well.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, cocoa and salt.
Add to sugar mixture.
Blend in chips and nuts.
Pour in a well-greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° until set. Note:
I sometimes put mixture in an unbaked pie shell.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut up cabbage and onion in casserole dish.
Put 1/2 butter over this.
Stir up egg, mayonnaise and soup; pour over cabbage. Crumble up crackers over this; pour rest of butter over mixture. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put sugar, margarine and evaporated milk in microwaveproof dish (a casserole, 1 1/2-quart, with a lid).
Cover and microwave on Roast for 10 minutes.
Remove from microwave and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Recover and put back in microwave and cook an additional 5 minutes on Roast.
Remove from microwave and stir in marshmallows, vanilla and chocolate chips or peanut butter.
Stir until all melted.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Slice rind in small thin pieces.
Soak overnight in lily lime. Rinse in the morning and put in boiler; cover with water and cook 3 hours.
Add green cake color, spices, vinegar and sugar; cook until tender.
Put in jars and seal.

title: chocolate and cheese dessert
directions: Mix flour, nuts and margarine together and crumble into a 9 x 13-inch
pan.
Pat	down with a spoon.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cover with water and cook until tender.

title: lily's meat loaf
directions: Mix the above ingredients together.
Scoop up a handful of ground beef mixture and make a ball, approximately the size of a baseball, and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Continue to do this until you have used all the mixture.
It makes 5 or 6 balls.
Pour approximately 1 cup of water in the pan.
Cook at 350° about 40 minutes or until the meat is brown.
Take pan out of oven and pour off the grease and water.
Pour or squirt ketchup over the top of each ball of meat and place back in the oven for about 5 minutes or until ketchup is set.
Leftovers make great sandwiches.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Drained, crushed pineapple may be added.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Mix rice, chicken soup, mushroom soup and water thoroughly. Pour in pan.
Push chicken pieces into rice mixture.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake about 15 minutes longer or until done.

title: fiesta sandwich
directions: Cut off the top 1/3 of loaf of bread and set aside.
Hollow out, leaving 1/2-inch thick crust all around.
Spread cut surfaces with bean dip.
Layer as follows: Colby Jack, half the red pepper, Monterey Jack with jalapenos, olive slices, tomato cubes, Cheddar and avocado.
Top with remainder of red pepper.
Combine shredded taco cheese with salad dressing and spoon on top.
Replace top of bread loaf.
Wrap tightly in foil and keep cool until ready to serve.
If desired, heat in oven or over coals to warm and melt cheese.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: polynesian chicken wings
directions: Cut up wings; discard tips.
Marinate overnight in teriyaki sauce mixture.
Next day, put chicken and sauce in pan.
Pour sweet and sour sauce over wings.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour. During the last 15 minutes, pour on the Hawaiian vegetables, including the sauce, and continue baking.
Serve with rice.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Saute onion in butter in large skillet until tender; add green pepper and remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 40 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: shrimp and wild rice
directions: Saute onions and green peppers in butter until tender.
Mix all together and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fried green beans
directions: Put corn meal, flour, garlic powder, salt and pepper in large plastic container with lid.
Add green beans.
Shake well until beans are completely coated.
Heat butter in skillet until bubbly. Add beans, cook over high heat, stirring occasionally.
Cook 10 minutes or until coating is crunchy and brown.
Serve hot, with extra butter if desired.

title: judy's italian casserole
directions: In a skillet, brown the beef with onion, garlic and seasonings; stir to separate meat.
Combine in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with soup, water and noodles.
Place the cheese around the edge of the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yields 4 servings.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar, cinnamon, soda, salt, flour and eggs in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Fold in strawberries.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain beans, place in bowl and add pepper and onion.
Mix oil and vinegar; add sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture and toss.
Refrigerate, covered, for 12 to 24 hours.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, flour, salt and nutmeg. Mix egg mixture into rhubarb.
Put into a deep pie pan with crust. Cover with crisscross crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pistachio nut cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together except syrup.
Mix for 10 minutes.
Grease Bundt pan and sprinkle with crushed walnuts and toasted coconut.
Take 1 cup batter and mix with syrup.
Divide remaining batter in half and place half in pan, then the layer of chocolate batter.
Bake at 350° for about 60 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Roll out and cut.
Drop into boiling broth.
Cook until done.

title: haluski with dumplings
directions: Chop cabbage and saute in butter.
While cooking, mix flour, eggs, salt, milk and 1/2 cup of water.
Add more water if needed. Drop small amounts in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain and add to cabbage.
Brown onion in butter and pour over cabbage and dumplings.

title: jam cake
directions: Beat the oil, sugar and eggs until creamy.
Add the jam and buttermilk.
Sift the flour with the salt, soda and spices.
Add to other ingredients.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in a tube pan about 1 hour at 325°.

title: no-peek stew
directions: Trim off all fat from meat.
Combine all ingredients in slow-cooker.
Cook, covered, at low heat setting for 9 to 10 hours.
Makes 8 cups, about 5 servings.

title: pesto tortellini
directions: Chop parsley in blender; with motor running, add nuts, garlic, basil and salt.
Process until garlic is chopped.
Slowly add olive oil.
Stop machine and fold in cheese.
Cook tortellini according to package directions.
Drain and toss with sauce. Serve at room temperature with toothpicks.
Garnish with chopped fresh tomatoes and basil.
Serves 12 (1/4 cup servings).

title: drop cookies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add cocoa, sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and oats.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: spicy roasted potatoes
directions: Cut washed potatoes (with or without skins) into 1-inch cubes. Do not blot dry.
Combine the rest of the ingredients in a plastic bag.
Toss potatoes in bag to coat them.
Evenly spread potatoes in one layer on lightly greased dish or pan.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Turn potatoes every 15 minutes.

title: you-name-it cake
directions: Follow directions on box of cake mix.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool.
Mix vanilla pudding, cream cheese and milk. Spread on cake.
Drain pineapple.
Spread on pudding mix. Top with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with pecans, if desired.

title: spareribs
directions: *For small portions use 2 tablespoons for every 8 ounces of tomato sauce.

title: seafoam frosting
directions: Boil until spins a thread in cold water.
Slowly add egg whites to syrup, beating at same time.

title: smoked salmon ball
directions: Place cream cheese in a large bowl.
Beat with an electric mixer set at med-high speed until smooth.
Add onion, lemon juice, 1 TBSP. parsley, horseradish, liquid smoke, garlic pwd. And salt to cream cheese and mix well.
Flake the salmon.
Stir salmon into cream cheese mixture.
Shape the salmon mix into 1 large ball or 2 small balls.
Combine pecans and remaining parsley in a small bowl.
Coat salmon ball with pecan mixture. Chill, tightly wrapped in plastic wrap, for 1 hour.
Serve with wheat crackers.

title: banana cooler
directions: Combine banana, buttermilk or yogurt, honey and lemon juice in blender and mix well.
Pour into chilled glass and garnish with lemon slice.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: french puffs
directions: Mix together thoroughly the shortening, sugar and egg.
Set aside.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add to shortening, sugar and egg mixture alternately with the 1/2 cup milk.
Fill muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Makes 10 to 12 muffins.
When thoroughly baked, roll in the melted butter and then in the sugar/cinnamon mixture.

title: wild plum muffins
