This cake is moist and keeps well for a long time, if nobody finds it.
If they do, it's a flash in the pan.

title: southwestern chicken with black bean salsa
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing well.
Store in covered jar.
Also good on shrimp.
Rub chicken breasts with seasoning.
Cook on grill until done.
Top with Black Bean Salsa.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Grease and flour sheet cake pan.
Pour 1/3 of cake mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° until tester is clean, about 11 to 15 minutes.
Melt caramels and margarine in milk.
Pour on top of cake.
Sprinkle chips and pecans on caramel mixture.
Pour rest of cake mix on top and bake 20 more minutes. Cut in squares.

title: swedish delights
directions: For dough, sift together flour, sugar and salt.
Stir in lemon peel.
Cut in butter as in pie crust.
Stir in sour cream with a fork until mixture holds together.
Knead with hands to combine. Form into a ball and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: pringle's candy
directions: Crush potato chips. Melt white bark. Stir in crushed chips and peanuts. Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet lined with wax paper on it. Let set until hard.

title: hamburger sour cream casserole
directions: In a casserole dish, add 1/2 noodles, 1/2 hamburger sauce, sour cream, cream cheese, hamburger and sauce and remaining noodles. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut toast
directions: In a bowl, combine the coconut, sugar, butter, egg and vanilla. Mix well, spread over each slice of bread. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Chop lettuce, onion and tomatoes.
Toss with cheese, dressing and hot sauce.
Crunch and add tortilla chips and avocado.
Brown ground beef and stir in beans and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Simmer 10 minutes and mix into salad and serve.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Pull crescent rolls apart.
Place one candy bite in the center of the roll.
Wrap the roll around the candy.
Bake for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven, cool.
Top with vanilla cake icing.

title: peppery beef and vegetables(low cholesterol and low-fat)
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
For sauce, in a small bowl, stir together water, soy sauce, cornstarch, pepper and red pepper.
Set aside.
Add 1 tablespoon oil to skillet or wok.
Heat over medium-high heat.
Add garlic and stir-fry for 30 seconds.
Add pea pods and red pepper; stir-fry 1 minute.
Add mushrooms.
Stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove vegetables from wok. Add 1 tablespoon oil to wok.
Stir-fry beef in hot oil for 3 to 4 minutes or until done.
Push beef to the side of pan.
Stir sauce and pour into the center of the wok.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Return vegetables to wok; cook and stir all ingredients 1 minute.
Toss with spaghetti.
Makes 4 servings.

title: celery seed salad dressing
directions: Beat sugar, salt and mustard with small amount of vinegar. Add oil very slowly.
Continue beating while adding oil.
Last add remaining vinegar and beat very well.
Add celery seed.

title: chicken-n-dumplings
directions: Heat water and broth to boiling.
Meanwhile, open and separate biscuits in large bowl with flour in it.
Coat all biscuits with flour.
Put onions in pot with water and add butter and salt and pepper.
Once water reaches boiling, pinch off biscuits into 4 to 5 pieces each, adding them to the water.
When pot is full, add chicken.
Cook at a simmer until done.
If needed, a mixture of water and flour may be used as a thickener.

title: poppy seed bread (cake)
directions: Blend all ingredients together and beat 10 minutes with mixer. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes for Bundt or tube pan (greased and floured).
For 2 bread pans, try 25 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: If
using for salad, chop ham, chicken, pecans, pickles, boiled
eggs
and
celery
in larger pieces; if for sandwiches, chop
a
little finer.
Add cayenne to taste, and enough mayonnaise to hold together.

title: sharp cheese spread
directions: Cut cheese into small pieces; also chop pepper.
Grind together in food processor or blender.
Blend in small amount of milk until creamy and smooth.

title: linguine and shrimp
directions: Cook linguine and drain.
Boil shrimp.
Heat dressing in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir-fry 8 to 10 minutes. Add shrimp.
Toss with linguine.
Serve.

title: nutty fruit salad
directions: Cut or dice bananas, apples and oranges.
Mix all together in a large bowl.
Add fruit cocktail and pecans.
Mix all together, then add Cool Whip.
Let set for 15 minutes in refrigerator. Ready to serve.

title: homemade bubbles(for children)
directions: Gently stir all ingredients together in a big plastic container.

title: key lime pie
directions: Whip condensed milk, limeade and food coloring until stiff. Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into prepared crust and chill until set.
Garnish with lime slices, if desired.

title: easter sweet bread
directions: In large bowl, put milk.
Slowly beat in sugar, salt and butter.
Then add eggs and 1 cup flour.
Mix in slowly.
Then add yeast mixture and mix well.
Add vanilla and lemon and mix.
Add rest of flour, little at a time.
Keep mixing until dough is soft. Grease large bowl.
Place dough in flour 1 hour.
Punch down. Let it rise for 30 minutes.
Then roll and braid; form into a circle.
Place on a cookie sheet for 30 minutes.
Brush 1 egg and 1 teaspoon milk.
Sprinkle colored candies all over.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli and corn casserole
directions: In a bowl combine beaten egg, broccoli, corn, onion, salt and pepper.
In a small saucepan melt margarine; add stuffing mix. Toss to coat.
Stir 3/4 cup of buttered stuffing in vegetable mixture.
Put in greased casserole.
Sprinkle with rest of stuffing mix. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: broccoli ham ring
directions: Assemble crescent rolls on baking stone or pan, overlapping wide ends.
This should look like a star: open, round circle in center with points facing out.

title: onion, orange and spinach salad
directions: Remove stems from spinach.
Wash and dry thoroughly.
Combine spinach, onions, oranges and celery in a large salad bowl.
Toss gently.
Combine remaining ingredients in a jar and shake vigorously.
Serve dressing with salad.

title: crawfish dip
directions: Saute peppers in butter, then add seasonings, parsley, Rotel tomatoes and crawfish.
Add a few chunks of cream cheese at a time, constantly stirring.
When the cheese is melted, it's ready! If this is too thick, you can cut it with whipping cream or half and half.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into ball.
Chill for two to three hours and then roll in pecan chips.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix and put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 35 minutes.

title: honey whole wheat bread
directions: Combine flour, milk, salt and yeast in large mixing bowl. Combine remaining ingredients, then add to dry ingredients (pour warm liquid over flour mixture). Blend at low speed 1 minute. By hand, stir in 1 cup whole-wheat flour. Add 4 to 4 1/2 cups all-purpose flour. Knead for 5 minutes. Place in a greased bowl; cover and let rise in a warm place 45 to 60 minutes or until light and double.

Punch dough down and divide into thirds for 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2 pans or in 1/2 for larger pans. Shape into loaf by rolling dough into rectangle. Roll up jelly roll fashion and place in greased pans. Cover and let rise 30 to 45 minutes in a warm place until light and doubled. Bake at 375° (350° glass pans) for 40 to 45 minutes, until loaf sounds hollow when tapped. Makes 3 loaves. Can freeze. Can do ahead.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch cake pan with whole graham crackers.
Mix pudding and mix together until real thick; add Cool Whip and mix well.
Spread mixture over graham crackers.
Top with another layer of crackers, then spread on chocolate frosting and refrigerate. Serve cool.

title: banana split pie
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick butter, melted. Press in bottom of 13 x 9-inch sheet cake pan.
Beat eggs, sugar and 2 sticks butter for 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour on top of crumbs. Slice bananas and layer on top of egg mixture.
Add layer of pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries, if desired.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix together and mold into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Can be frozen.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Sift together the flour and soda.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake in well-greased and floured pan at 350° for almost 1 hour.

title: miniature pecan tarts
directions: Stir together cream cheese, 1/2 cup butter and flour until smooth.
Shape into 24 balls.
Place in ungreased miniature muffin cups.
Press dough into bottom and around sides of cups to form into small shells.

title: udder (healing) baum
directions: Warm jelly in warm pan of water over low
heat and stir in other 2 ingredients.
Fill into small jars.

title: fluffy potato doughnuts
directions: Beat until light eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add potatoes and shortening; set aside.
Sift dry ingredients together, then add alternately with milk to potato mixture, beating well.
Chill dough 3 hours (if desired).
Roll to 3/8-inch thickness.

title: meat and potato pie
directions: Combine meat, milk, soup mix, salt and pepper.
Mix gently and put into 1 pie crust.
Top with potatoes.
Place other pie crust on top of potatoes.
Seal and flute edge.
Cut design in top crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sloppy joe sandwiches(cooking for a crowd)
directions: Brown beef and drain fat.
Add the next 7 ingredients.
Simmer or cook in an electric roaster for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally. Serve on buns.
Makes 100 servings.

title: brownies(old german recipe)
directions: Mix all in 8 x 8-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: date loaf
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk. Add dates, nuts and 1/2 of the crumbs.
Pour out on the rest of the cracker crumbs.
Knead and shape into loaf. Wrap in foil and place in refrigerator.
Serve thinly sliced with Cool Whip or whipped cream, topped with a cherry.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until crisp-tender.
Mix broccoli with dry rice, soups and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Stir and serve. Could add chopped ham or turkey before baking.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions together until done and drain. Cook noodles and drain.
Mix all ingredients; top with 1 package of crushed crackers and 1 stick of melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: christmas pot cheese balls (zeppole)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into about 2 inches of hot vegetable oil.
Drain on paper towel after browning.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: oven baked fish
directions: Place fillets on baking dish and brush with Italian dressing. Bake until fish flakes.

title: easy supper dish
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Add macaroni and stir thoroughly.
Add tomato juice.
Bring to a rapid boil.
Reduce heat and cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and cover.
Serve when cheese is melted.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown meat, drain.
Stir in sauce and seasoning mix.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Unroll dough and press into bottom and sides of ungreased 12-inch pizza pan.
Prick bottom & sides with fork.
Bake 10 - 12 min. until golden brown.
Cover top with meat mixture, top with cheese.
Continue baking until cheese begins to melt.
Top with remaining ingredients and serve with sour cream.

title: chocolate chunk blondies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease square pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
In large mixer bowl cream butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts, if desired, and chocolate chunks.
Spread into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool completely; cut into bars.

title: mexican salad
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in kidney beans, salad dressing, water and chili powder.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Shred 8 ounces Cheddar cheese.
Combine lettuce and sliced green onions.
Add meat sauce and 1 1/2 cups shredded Cheddar cheese.
Toss lightly and sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: mock eclair
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Blend in Cool Whip. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with butter.
Line with graham crackers. Pour half of pudding mixture over crackers.
Then add another layer of crackers.
Pour remaining pudding over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: chicken teriyaki(serves 4)
directions: Heat heavy frying pan.
Grease it with vegetable oil.
Add chicken and saute over high heat evenly until it gets golden brown on both sides.
Combine seasonings for teriyaki sauce.
Drain oil from frying pan.
Pour teriyaki sauce over chicken and cook, covered tightly, over low heat for about 7 minutes.
Turn chicken pieces twice while cooking.
Increase heat and continue cooking, uncovered, glazing chicken on both sides with teriyaki sauce. Reserve some of the sauce to top the chicken when served.

title: sour cream sugar cookies
directions: In one bowl, beat together shortening, sugar, eggs, vanilla and sour cream.
In a very large bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and nutmeg or cinnamon.
Pour the contents of the first bowl into the sifted ingredients.
Stir until well mixed but do not beat.
Cover and put in refrigerator for 30 minutes. Preheat oven to 400°.
Scoop out 1/4 of the dough at a time onto a well-floured surface.
Sprinkle with flour and roll to approximately 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut out with floured cookie cutters.
Sprinkle with colored sugar, if desired.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets for 6 to 8 minutes until slightly golden. Cool on a wire rack.
Decorate with icing, if desired.
Makes 4 or 5 dozen.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with chopped tomatoes, green onions and grated Cheddar cheese.
Serve with plain Doritos.

title: hawaiian pork luau
directions: Drain sliced pineapple reserving juice; measure 1/4 cup juice. Add water to remaining juice to make 1 3/4 cups.
Set aside. Moisten pork chops with the 1/4 cup juice.
Empty Shake 'n Bake into plastic bag; mix ginger.
Shake pork chops until evenly coated.
Arrange pork chops in single layer in shallow baking dish; place 1 pineapple slice on each pork chop.
Dice remaining pineapple and set aside.
Bake pork chops at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: cracker jack
directions: Cook to hard boil.
Pour over popped corn.

title: sweet pickles(14 days)
directions: Step 1:
Add 4 cups canning or pickling salt to 2 gallons of fresh water.
Fill 4 gallon churn with whole cucumbers.
Pour water and salt over cucumbers and let stand for 7 days.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Add sugar and vanilla to beaten egg whites.
Beat again until firm.
Stir in pecans and crackers.
Pour into greased pie pan. Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: banana caramel pie
directions: Put opened can of Eagle Brand milk in boiler.
Add water until it is 1 1/2 inches on can.
Continue to boil for 4 to 5 hours.
Do not let water in boiler cook all the way down.
When milk is caramelized, remove from heat and let cool.
Slice bananas and place in cooked pie shell.
Pour caramel over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.
Grate Heath bars and sprinkle on top.

title: eagle brand brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use 8-inch square baking pan.
Place margarine in pan and melt in oven.
Take out and add in this order:
graham cracker crumbs, butterscotch morsels, chocolate chips.
Pour Eagle Brand sweetened condensed milk over top.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Cool completely before slicing into bars.

title: sweet potato cake squares
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add sweet potatoes and vanilla, mixing well.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Combine flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to sweet potato mixture and mix well.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix together and season to taste.

title: pork with apricot dressing
directions: Brown chops in butter; remove from pan and add onion to brown. When brown, add mixed mustard, vinegar and apricot jam.
Cook until hot; add chops and serve over cooked rice.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant; cube and cook until tender in salt water. Drain thoroughly.
Mash and season to taste.
Mash tomatoes and mix with eggplant, onion, eggs and cornbread crumbs.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Add enough milk to cover well.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheddar baked potatoes
directions: In a small bowl, combine soup, paprika, onion and pepper.
In a greased 2-quart baking dish, arrange potatoes in overlapping rows.
Sprinkle with cheese; spoon soup mixture over cheese. Cover; bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Uncover; bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Potatoes should be fork-tender.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix and pour into buttered casserole dish the sweet potatoes, milk, 1/2 cup butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Mix brown sugar, flour, 1/3 cup melted butter and 1 cup nuts and pour on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: heavenly chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
You will need 3 (9-inch) round pans.

title: sausage cheddar quiche
directions: Cover quiche dish with crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Cook sausage and drain.
Combine next 7 ingredients, mixing well. Spoon into shell and top with cheese.
Combine milk and eggs, beating until foamy.
Pour over cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Dice chicken and spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix sour cream and soup together and pour over chicken.
Mix 1 box Stove Top stuffing according to directions on box.
Spread over chicken. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Bake pastry shell at 350° for 5 minutes; set aside.
Combine eggs and next 6 ingredients in a medium bowl and stir well.
Spoon egg mixture evenly into prepared pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Garnish with whipped cream.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease Bundt pan.
Cut biscuits in 4 pieces.
Roll biscuit pieces in sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pack pieces into Bundt pan.
Melt butter or margarine.
Stir in brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Wait 5 minutes and turn out of pan.
Pull hunks off and eat.

title: baptist pie
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Add lemon juice.
Mix well; stir in milk, then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour over crust and sprinkle on the nuts.
Garnish with more oranges.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours before serving.

title: hummus
directions: Drain the chickpeas, then proceed to create a fluid and smooth form of chickpea mash in a food processor.
Add the garlic, lemon juice, tahini and salt to your liking.
Be sure that the amount of tahini is sparingly added.
Too much will create a soupy and gritty oil spill.
Serve with pita bread or on vegetables (i.e., tomatoes).

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Boil, remove from heat and add 3 1/2 tablespoons strawberry jello.
Cool, add 1 quart strawberries.

title: terry's chocolate pie
directions: Mix together egg yolks, sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add some warm milk to dry ingredients, then mix well.
Add mixture to remaining milk.
Stir constantly on medium heat until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill.

title: granola
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand in large bowl.
Spread evenly on cookie sheets.
Bake at 275° until coconut is lightly browned (approximately 1 hour).
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: three-step salad
directions: In a small saucepan over medium heat, cook and stir almonds and sugar until almonds are coated and lightly browned, about 4 minutes.
Spread the almonds on heavy-duty foil to cool; gently break apart.
In a large salad bowl, combine romaine, oranges, celery and onions.
Top with almonds.
In a jar with a tight-fitting lid, combine the oil, vinegar, sugar, salt, dry mustard, and garlic powder; shake well. Pour over the salad and toss gently.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery; brown ground beef.
Add tomato soup, ketchup, Worcestershire, mushroom soup and Tabasco. Simmer all together until well blended.
Cook spaghetti noodles according to package directions.
In casserole, layer noodles and sauce and sprinkle with grated sharp cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbles.

title: jello dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and boiling water until dissolved.
Add ice cubes; let melt.
Then add by spooning in the vanilla ice cream. Let set in refrigerator.

title: cheesy chili dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into 1-quart casserole.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir before serving.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: oreo freakout
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, crumble Oreo cookies by hand; reserve 4 or 5 for later.
Slice ice cream in 1/2-inch slices; layer on cookies.
Pour Hershey's syrup over ice cream; sprinkle nuts over syrup.
Spread Cool Whip over nuts.
Crumble remaining cookies over Cool Whip.
Put in freezer at least 1 hour.
Serve and enjoy.

title: no roll sugar cookies
directions: Mix together into a dough.
Put in the refrigerator over night and pinch off in small balls.
Space on cookie sheet.
Put about a cup of sugar in a bowl and dip the bottom of a glass in the sugar and press the cookie dough and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until as brown as desired.
Remove immediately to cool. Store in an airtight container.

title: cheese broccoli soup
directions: Steam broccoli until tender; cut into pieces.
Place half and half and water in top of double boiler.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Heat until cheese is melted; add broccoli.
Mix cornstarch and water.
Add to soup and heat until thickened.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and one egg at a time.
Add flour and extract.
Fold in 7-Up.
Cook at 325° for one hour and fifteen minutes in a Bundt cake pan.

title: date filled wontons
directions: To prepare the date filling, in small saucepan, combine dates, granulated sugar and water. Bring to a boil. Cook, stirring constantly, over low heat about 4 minutes or until thickened. Remove from heat.
Stir in walnuts, lemon or orange juice and vanilla. Cool date filling.

title: chicken breasts lorraine
directions: Crumble beef
into bottom of unbuttered casserole.
Lay chicken breasts on	top.
Cover
with
soup, sour cream, onion and pepper.
Mix a little with a fork.	Do not cover.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours
(turn	to 250° after 20 minutes).
If starts to brown too much
on
top, reduce temperature 25°.

title: polenta
directions: Place smoked sausage in a large saucepan.
Cover with water and boil.
Place cornmeal, Parmesan cheese and garlic salt in a mixing bowl.
Stir in cold water to make a thin paste.
Take sausages out of pan, leave water in pan and return to a boil. Stir in cornmeal mixture and cook until thickened.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream oleo,
Crisco and 2 cups sugar well.
Reserve 1/2 cup sugar for
egg
whites.
Add 1 egg yolk at a time, beating well after each.
Sift and measure flour;
add salt and baking powder. Add
soda
to
buttermilk and dissolve.
Begin adding flour mixture and add alternately with buttermilk, ending with flour. Add
flavoring.
Beat
egg	whites	and
1/2 cup sugar until stiff peaks form.
Fold into cake mixture.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: italian pepper sandwich
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and tomato in salad dressing until soft. Cut rolls and butter. Place meat on roll bottoms; cover with cooked vegetable mixture and top with cheese slices. Broil 3 to 4 minutes or until cheese melts and buttered side of roll top is lightly browned. Close sandwich and serve.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes. Frost with chocolate frosting or dust with powdered sugar.

title: apple pie(crust and filling)
directions: Measure flour and salt into bowl.
Cut in shortening thoroughly.
Sprinkle with water, 1 tablespoon at a time, mixing until all flour is moistened and dough almost cleans side of bowl (1 or 2 more tablespoons of water can be added if needed.)
Gather dough into ball; shape into flattened round on lightly floured cloth-covered board.
With flour covered rolling pin, roll dough 2-inches larger than inverted pie pan.
Fold pastry into quarters; unfold and ease into pan.
Trim overhang edge of pastry 1-inch from rim of the pan.
Fold and roll pastry edges under, even with pan; flute.
Fill and bake as directed in recipe.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and chili powder together.
Drain grease.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish with chips.
Spread meat over chips. Add another layer of chips.
Spread beans and chop onion over chips.
Add another layer of chips.
Spread soup over these. Slice cheese on top and pour Ro-Tel over it.
Bake in 350° oven, covered with foil for 45 minutes.

title: microwave cheesy chili dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a microwavable 1-quart casserole. Microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring every 4 minutes. Serve hot.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together the ingredients and put in baking dish.
Put the remaining half of the stuffing on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet pickles(14 days)
directions: Into a clean stone jar put 2 gallons of cucumbers, washed and sliced lengthwise. Regardless of size, cucumbers must be sliced or they will shrivel. Dissolve 2 cups of salt in one gallon of boiling water and pour while hot over pickles. Then cover and weight down pickles and let stand for 1 week.
Remove scum daily.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut cup of chicken into small pieces and put in bottom of casserole dish (2 1/2-inches high).
Mix chicken broth, soup and chopped onion.
Pour over chicken.
Mix the rest together and pour over top crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; cover.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Beat butter until creamy; gradually add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Blend in vanilla and eggs.
Add oats mixture; mix well.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured 9-inch pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. (Frosting mix and cake together.)

title: kids stuff
directions: Melt in microwave. Pour over box of Crispix or Rice Chex until well coated. Dump 2 cups powdered sugar into brown paper sack. Add cereal mixture and shake.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown meat on top of the stove in a large frying pan.
Place browned meat and remaining ingredients in a pressure cooker. Cover; lock and weight pressure cooker.
Cook on high until pressure is up, then reduce heat and cook for 45 minutes.
Let stand until pressure is reduced.

title: butterscotch haystacks
directions: Melt chips in double boiler.
When melted, add potatoes and peanuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Cover with water; bring to a boil for 2 minutes and cover.
Cool for 1 hour.
Drain.
Add water, tomatoes, onion, garlic and celery; simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Add remaining ingredients and heat to boiling.
Serves 10.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg white until it stands in soft peaks.
Gradually mix in brown sugar and vanilla.
Fold in pecan halves until well coated in egg-sugar mixture.
Place pecan halves on well-greased cookie sheet about 1 inch apart.
Bake in a 250° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn oven off and let set for 30 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: best punch ever
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into empty clean gallon milk jugs, not all the way to top (3/4 full).
Freeze.
Best if done 1 week before needed or longer.
Remove from freezer; let punch sit out for few hours before serving.
Serve slushy.	Do not add anything else to punch.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done; drain and rinse with cold water. Mix in large bowl onion, celery, green pepper and eggs.
Add macaroni, shrimp and crabmeat or lobster meat.
Stir in Miracle Whip; add mustard.
Mix well all ingredients.
Add salt, pepper and seasoning salt to taste.
Makes a great dish for cookouts. Serves 10.

title: pink potato salad
directions: Place in bowl: cubed potatoes, chopped onion, diced celery and sliced radishes. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Mix lightly with French Dressing. Chill in refrigerator. Remove bowl. Toss carefully with salad dressing and sweet pickle relish and mustard. Blend in hard cooked eggs, and minced parsley. Serve in bowl. Garnish with paprika. Serves 6.

title: tasty chicken
directions: Skin chicken and cut into bite sized pieces.
Saute onions and sliced peppers until soft.
Flour chicken.
Add salt and pepper. Add to vegetables and stir for 5 minutes.
Add ketchup, water and sugar.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked white rice.

title: broccoli-rice casserole elegante
directions: Boil broccoli and onion in small amount of water over low heat only until crisp.
Drain.
Add Cheez Whiz and soup to broccoli and onion in warm pan.
Add margarine.
Stir until blended.
Add cooked rice and chestnuts.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Top with sharp shredded cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: meringue kisses
directions: Line 2 cookie sheets with foil.

In small bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar until soft peaks form, beating at high speed. Gradually sprinkle in sugar 2 tablespoons at a time, beating well after each addition until sugar completely dissolves and whites stand in stiff glossy peaks.
Preheat oven to 200°.
Spoon meringue into large decorating tube.
Pipe onto cookie sheet into mounds about 1 1/2 hours.
Turn oven off; let cookies stand in oven 30 minutes.
Cool completely on rack.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch dish.
Press biscuits down as crust. Spread 1 jar Ragu pizza sauce over biscuits; top with browned ground meat and onion.
Add pepperoni and black olives.
Salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Cover meat with cheeses. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° (uncovered) for 20 minutes or until
done.

title: cheesy squash bake
directions: In large skillet, saute squash and onions in butter for 15 minutes, or until tender; remove from heat.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper, if desired.
Combine egg and sour cream; stir in half the bacon.
Add to squash mixture and blend.
Spoon half of the squash mixture into a buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle Swiss cheese over top; spoon squash mixture over cheese. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese and remaining bacon on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Yields 6 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage, beef, salt and pepper.
Make into 1-inch balls.
Brown in shortening; drain and let cool.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Coat sausage balls with mashed potatoes.
Dip in egg mixture and roll in bread crumbs.
Let set 30 minutes. Deep-fry until golden brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Grease large casserole dish. Sprinkle 1/2 of poultry seasoning in bottom of casserole. Combine all other ingredients and pour over stuffing. Top with remaining stuffing. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: seasoned snack crackers
directions: Mix all together and pour over 1 bag Keebler Zesta oyster crackers in plastic covered bowl.
Stir or shake several times.

title: pickle relish
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and cloves.
Cover with 1/3 cup salt and ice cubes.
Let stand for 3 hours.
Mix vinegar, sugar and turmeric.
Let this come to a boil.
Put in vegetable mixture; simmer 15 minutes.
Put into jars and seal.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Break cake into small pieces.
Arrange a layer of cake in bottom of deep bowl.
Mix pineapple, cherries and nuts together in a bowl.
Toast coconut in a skillet on stovetop by stirring over low heat until brown; set aside to cool.
On the layer of cake spread the fruit mixture, then layer of coconut.
Then a layer of thawed topping.
Then repeat until everything is used up and finish topping by adding coconut as final item.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Saute onions.
Add soup and juice from can of mushrooms.
Blend together.
Pour over cooked rice in casserole.
Add layer of cheese, drained mushrooms and almonds. Bake at 350° until heated through.
Serves 10.

title: deep fried dutch apple cake
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil or shortening to a depth of 1/2-inch.
Beat egg with 1/4-cup milk.
Use rotary beater or whisk. Do not overbeat.
Add flour alternately with the milk and mix thoroughly using a slotted spoon; ending with milk.
Stir in apples.
Pour into hot oil.
Fry on both sides until golden brown; sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add beef, soup and beans in casserole dish.
Mix and add salt and pepper.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: christmas crunch
directions: Microwave the white chocolate for 1 minute.
Then stir each minute until melted.
It takes about 3 minutes.
Stir in crushed peppermint candy. Line a cookie sheet with waxed paper and spread the white chocolate mixture on the cookie sheet.
Place it in the freezer for 12 minutes.
Take out and break in pieces.

title: caramel dip and apples
directions: Core and slice apples.
Place in a large container of cold water and lemon juice to prevent fruit from browning until ready to serve.

title: key lime tart with lime ricky sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in bowl and mix completely.
Place one ounce of graham crackers in 8 flan rings or ramekins.

title: butter horns
directions: Blend well.
Divide dough into several round balls. Refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the first four ingredients thoroughly and spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine stuffing and margarine and spread on top of vegetable mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until hot all through.

title: peach pie
directions: Melt butter in square pan. Mix flour, sugar, milk, baking powder, salt and vanilla flavoring. Pour over melted butter. Pour peaches with juice over batter. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown. Make sure the batter rises. When batter rises, sprinkle a little sugar on pie.

title: buttermilk chess pie
directions: Cream sugar and melted margarine.
Add flour, salt and buttermilk.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until firm (about 45 minutes).

title: granny's apple pie
directions: Mix all together.
Put in pie shell.
Put pie crust on top. Make slits so steam can escape.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: hush puppies
directions: First off, heat up about 1/2 inch of cooking oil to about 360°.
While it's heating, mix corn meal, baking powder and salt. Then add the onions.
Blend in milk and water, maybe adding a little corn meal, if necessary, until the dough is stiff enough to be handled.
Shape the dough into oblong thumb-size cakes and drop into the fat.
Turn them occasionally until well browned.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with salt, pepper and onion.
Drain well.
Mix chicken soup and sour cream with squash.
Add grated carrot to squash mixture.
Melt oleo in a pan and mix dressing mix in oleo. Pat half in bottom of dish.
Pour squash mixture on top of dressing crust.
Sprinkle remainder of dressing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Bake at 350° in Bundt pan or tube pan until done.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 loaf pans, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Blend in dry ingredients, except for the nuts and fruit.
Mix well, then add nuts and fruit.
Bake in greased and floured pans for 65 to 75 minutes.

title: pasta delite(excellent dish for company or the family.)
directions: In a large skillet or saucepan, heat the oil with the garlic and shallots over moderate heat.
When they sizzle, add the tomatoes, breaking them up with your hands.
Crumble in the Ricotta cheese and stir in the sugar, basil and oregano.
Simmer until the sauce is thick, but still slightly liquid, 7 to 10 minutes.

title: comforting chicken noodle soup
directions: In large saucepan, bring water and bouillon to boil. Add noodles and cook until tender. DO NOT DRAIN. Add soup and chicken. Heat through. Remove from heat. Stir in sour cream and sprinkle with parsley.

title: crunchy salmon patties
directions: Add egg to drained salmon.
Salt and pepper and add enough flour to hold patties together.
Form into patties.
Roll in corn meal and fry until really crunchy.

title: green rice
directions: Beat 2 eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place these ingredients in a baking dish (or ring mold) which has been well-greased with 2 to 3 tablespoons of olive oil.
Bake in moderate oven at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.
The ring center or top may be covered with creamed mushrooms, creamed chicken or tuna or buttered vegetable.

title: oatmeal crispies (cookies)
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Add dry ingredients, oats and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: shortbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and mix well.
Spread on a 13 x 9-inch cookie sheet.
Prick top all over with a fork.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours, turn off oven.
Remove shortbread, cut into squares and sprinkle with sugar.
Return to oven and leave until oven cools.
Store in airtight container.
Will keep for weeks.
Freezes well.

title: kentucky cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together to cake batter consistency.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan or greased muffin tins.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: tuna ball
directions: Drain and flake tuna in bowl.
Add cream cheese; mix well. Add onion, bacon bits and seasonings; mix well.
Shape into ball; roll in parsley flakes.
Serve with Club crackers.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and sweet pepper.
Drain.
Add beans, brown sugar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and ketchup.
Cook in crock-pot for 3 hours on high.

title: thirty minute spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground chuck in heavy pot.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.
All ingredients should be altered to taste. The amounts given are only estimates as I never measure for my sauce.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix
graham
crackers,	butter	and 2 tablespoons sugar thoroughly.
Press onto bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: chicken with 40 cloves of garlic
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large Dutch oven, melt margarine in oil.
Add cut-up chicken, turning until golden (5 to 10 minutes). Tilt pan and spoon off all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Add garlic and stir.
Sprinkle with lemon, thyme, salt, pepper and water.
Cover tightly and bake 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and salt.
Add 1/4 cup milk.
Bring to boil and boil 1 minute.
Turn off heat but leave pan on the stove for 5 minutes.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Mix pudding with 3 3/4 cups milk.
Add Cool Whip.

title: potted shrimp sandwich spread
directions: Mince the shrimp and mix with butter. Add the other ingredients. Makes approximately 1 1/4 cups.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Spread in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer ham and cheese over broccoli.
Beat remaining ingredients with hand mixer until smooth.
Slowly pour over cheese. Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: church windows
directions: Melt chocolate chips, butter or margarine and paraffin.
Cool slightly.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Shape into logs on aluminum foil; sprinkle with coconut and roll.
Store in fridge. Slice when wanted.

title: heavenly delight
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix flour, margarine, milk and pecans and put into bottom of greased pan, 10 x 13 x 2-inch.
Preheat oven.
Cook about 25 to 35 minutes.
Let cool.

title: cashew chicken
directions: In a small bowl, place chicken strips with 2 tablespoons soy sauce and 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
Blend well.
Let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil with 1/2 teaspoon salt, in wok over high heat.
Add chicken strips and stir-fry until white and firm.
Add onion and mushroom.
Cook until vegetables are soft.
Remove from wok.
Add remaining 2 tablespoons of oil, cabbage and sugar.
Stir-fry about 3 or 4 minutes, until cabbage is crisp-tender.
Return chicken-vegetable mixture to wok. Add cashews and toss, add 1 teaspoon cornstarch to 1/4 cup soy sauce.
Stir into the chicken mixture.
Cover and steam 1 minute, uncover and stir until sauce is thickened.
Serve with Chinese noodles.

title: gerrell's sour cream cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese with an electric mixer until light and fluffy; gradually add sugar, mixing well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition; stir in vanilla.
Fold sour cream into cream cheese mixture and pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 500° for 8 minutes.
Reduce heat to 225° and bake 50 minutes.
Turn off oven; open oven door slightly and let cheesecake stand in oven for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven; let cool to room temperature on a wire rack.
Chill 8 hours or overnight.
Garnish as desired. Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: graham cracker goodies
directions: Put a layer of graham crackers in a 17 1/2 x 11 1/2 pan. Cook remaining ingredients slowly, until thickened about 15 minutes. Spread over graham crackers then put another layer of crackers.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix pineapple, pie filling, cake mix, coconut and pecans. Then pour butter on top and bake 45 minutes at 300 to 350°.

title: lasagna supreme
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions.
Drain; set aside.
Cook ground beef, garlic and onion in a large skillet over medium heat until meat is browned, stirring until meat crumbles.
Drain well.
Wipe pan drippings from skillet with paper towel.
Combine Paul Newman's socarooni sauce with meat.
Let simmer 20 minutes.
Combine eggs and next 4 ingredients; set aside.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Prepare Dream Whip according to directions on box. Mix this with cream cheese mixture.
In a pan, put a layer of graham cracker crumbs, then a layer of 1 can of pie filling.
Top this with Dream Whip mixture.
Repeat.

title: marinade for turkey, chicken, pork chops or steak
directions: Mix all ingredients together in blender.
Marinate meat several hours or overnight.

title: mole poblano
directions: Remove cooked chicken from broth and set aside, keeping chicken warm.
Reserve broth.
Slice chilies open and remove seeds.
Toast chilies in a preheated oven, just enough not to burn.
Toast bread on griddle of stove, just enough to brown.
In frying pan, fry sesame seed in 1/4 cup oil.
Remove seed and set aside.
Add 1/4 cup oil to pan and fry onion until tender.
Set aside.
Toast tomato on griddle, then peel off skin.
Be sure to follow instructions carefully to have a good tasting mole.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Chill.
Garnish with more orange sections, if desired.
Makes 3 1/2 cups or 6 servings.

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix
together.	Spoon
on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Boil sugar and corn
syrup
together
about
2 minutes. Pour slowly over beaten eggs, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla.
Put pecans
in
bottom
of uncooked crust.
Pour mixture over pecans.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: country living fudge(easy breezy to make)
directions: Line 8-inch square pan with wax paper or foil.
Combine in pot chips, milk, salt on low heat until chips melt.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and nuts.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain.
Add potatoes and juice.
Simmer for 20 minutes, or until potatoes are cooked.
Add clams, crabmeat, shrimp, milk, half and half, creamed corn, salt, pepper and thyme to taste; add parsley.
Cook until it starts to boil. One-half cup wine is optional.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Put meat and other ingredients in crock-pot in order given and cook on slow heat for 8 hours.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Roll pineapple in sour cream.
Then roll in coconut.
Put toothpick in each chunk and freeze.
Great for parties.

title: old fashion lace cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and sugar. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Drop 1/4 teaspoonful of batter 4-inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden.
Let cool before removing. Makes 4 dozen.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix
together
butter,
sugar
and
eggs.
Beat
until slightly lumpy only.
Stir in crushed pineapple with juice and cubed bread.
Bake
in a greased 1 1/2 quart casserole, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg and cinnamon.
Beat thoroughly.
Fold in grated apples.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour (preheat oven).

title: chum casserole
directions: Fry meat, onion and peppers together until peppers and onions are almost done.
Cook noodles in salt water until done; drain. Mix all together in casserole.
Top with bread crumbs if desired. Bake in a 350° oven until done.
If it is too thick before serving, add some hot milk.

title: welsh cookies(36)
directions: Cream
sugar, oleo and shortening together.
Add beaten eggs to the creamed mixture.
Sift all dry ingredients together. Combine
creamed
mixture,	dry
ingredients, raisins and milk to form a soft dough.	Gently roll a portion of dough to 1/4-inch thickness;	cut
with
round
cookie cutter.
Fry on skillet
at 350° for 3 minutes on each side.
Sprinkle lightly with granulated sugar while cooking.

title: cream caramel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare 3 (9-inch) cake pans.
Cream margarine or butter until light.
Add sugar gradually until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together.
Add about 1/4 of the flour mixture, beating until thoroughly mixed.
Add 1/3 sour cream and combine thoroughly.
Repeat, alternating flour and sour cream.
Begin and end with flour.
Stir in flavoring.
Pour into prepared pans.
Place in preheated oven and bake for 25 to 35 minutes.
Test for doneness.
Remove onto cake racks when done. Cool 10 minutes and carefully remove from pans.
Frost with Caramel Frosting.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Beat all ingredients together and pour into oiled 9 X 13 pan.

title: pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a large spring-form tube pan.
Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Do not preheat oven.
Put all the ingredients into a large bowl; blend all ingredients.
Beat with electric mixer for 5 1/2 minutes at medium speed.
After placing pan in oven, set temperature at 350°.
Bake for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: chicken divine
directions: Butter baking dish.
Boil chicken until done.
Place chicken, then broccoli in dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken and broccoli.
Garnish with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbling brown.

title: real lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together.
Add cold water.
Cook in microwave, stirring often.
When it is a medium consistency, add egg yolks, lemon juice and rind.
Return to microwave and cook until thick.
If too thick, use hand blender to smooth out.
Add margarine.
Pour into pie crust.
Beat egg whites and 1/3 cup sugar.
Spread meringue to hot pie, sealing to sides.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs (well beaten).
Add syrup and flour.
Mix together thoroughly.
Add nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake one hour at 300°.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Combine all ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Then mix 1 package Bisquick until it forms paste.
Cover top of pie.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Dot with butter and let brown.

title: puppy chow snack
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Stir in Rice Chex.
Put 2 cups powdered sugar in bag; add Chex mixture and shake until coated.
Spread mixture on cookie sheet to dry.

title: breakfast scones
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Put parchment paper on baking sheet. Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Using paddles at low speed, add butter cubes and mix until nearly blended.
Add fruit.

title: turkey casserole with cheese
directions: Melt fat in skillet.
Add onion and brown.
Add water or broth, rice, salt and pepper.
Cook for 20 minutes or until rice is done.
Add turkey and cheese. Heat until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Put greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 1/2 hours before baking.
Let stand at room temperature.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Cover mixture with croutons. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheesecake tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients except wafers.
Place vanilla wafer in bottom of baking cup liners.
Fill 3/4 full with cheese mixture. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool in refrigerator.
Top with any fruit filling.
Makes 18 tarts.

title: layered dessert
directions: Mix well together and pat into 11 x 13 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: wine rice
directions: Mix ingredients and cook in double boiler 45 minutes.
Add sugar and sprinkle cinnamon on top when served.

title: oreo shazam bars
directions: Finely roll 20 cookies. Mix cookie crumbs and butter; spread over the bottom of a 9 x 9 x 2 baking pan, pressing lightly. Chop remaining cookies. Layer coconut, white chips and chopped cookies in prepared pan. Drizzle evenly with condensed milk. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown and set. Cool completely; cut into bars. Makes 24 bars.

title: ice cream kahlua cake
directions: If you like chocolate and Heath bars, you will love this dessert.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cover hamburger with cold water (4 cups) and simmer until meat loses pink color. Drain. Add celery, onion and vegetables. Cook slowly until vegetables are done. Add tomatoes and chicken noodle soup mix. Simmer 30 minutes.
